On Sun, Jun 15, 2008 at 22:37:00 +0200, Jens Schweikhardt wrote:

> # Set LC_CTYPE and LC_COLLATE.
> 
> Thanks Thomas, that did the trick:

You're welcome.

> (Note to readers: this is on FreeBSD; the available locales can be found
> in directory /usr/share/locale).

This directory contains all locales installed with applications, however
on Linux glibc can be stripped out of some of them. The most reliable
source of that information is:

locale -a

as /usr/lib/locale may contain single locale-archive file instead of
old-fashioned per-locale files.

